Using django_select2 autocompletes in django_grappelli works pretty well, except for some styling issues which are probably caused by the "!important" grapelli styles.

This rule from [screen.css](https://github.com/sehmaschine/django-grappelli/blob/master/grappelli/static/grappelli/stylesheets/screen.css) causes some unsightly overlap, e.g. in the [select2_modelform](https://django-easy-select2.readthedocs.io/en/latest/reference.html#easy_select2.utils.select2_modelform) dropdown widget:

```
.grp-tools.grp-related-widget-tools {
    position: absolute;
    right: -30px;
    top: 2px;
    z-index: 1;
```

![grap_bad](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/762815/53068612-0f128200-3514-11e9-8471-c1e56b1da09c.png)

Disabling `position` and `right` rules in the browser rectifies the layout temporarily:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/762815/53068656-2f424100-3514-11e9-8239-89e5e8582d97.png)

A temporary fix is to override the style in a custom `admin/change_form.html`:
```
{% extends "admin/change_form.html" %}
{% load staticfiles %}

{% block stylesheets %}
{{ block.super }}
<link rel="shortcut icon" href="{% static 'images/favicon.ico' %}"><! -- favicon -->
<style>
.grp-tools.grp-related-widget-tools {position: relative; right: 0px;}
</style>
{% endblock %}
```

